h3cVoSIP.name: h3cVoSIP

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cVoSIP.contactinfo: Platform Team Huawei 3Com Technologies co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
h3cVoSIP.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the SIP client configuration. Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) is an application layer control protocol that can establish, modify, and terminate multimedia sessions such as IP phone calls, multimedia distribution, and multimedia conferences.

h3cSIPID.name: h3cSIPID
h3cSIPID.description: The unique identification of a SIP gateway. This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPPasswordType.name: h3cSIPPasswordType
h3cSIPPasswordType.description: The display type of a SIP gateway password. By default, this object should have the value simple(1). This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPPassword.name: h3cSIPPassword
h3cSIPPassword.description: A SIP gateway password. This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPSourceIPAddressType.name: h3cSIPSourceIPAddressType
h3cSIPSourceIPAddressType.description: The source IP address type of the local peer acting as UA (User Agent). This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPSourceIP.name: h3cSIPSourceIP
h3cSIPSourceIP.description: The source IP address of the local peer acting as UA (User Agent). This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPRegisterMode.name: h3cSIPRegisterMode
h3cSIPRegisterMode.description: The object describes the method to send the type of telephone number. gatewayAll The register mode is gateway mode and the register message contains all the POTS numbers. gatewaySingle The register mode is gateway mode and every register message contains only one POTS number. phoneNumber The register mode is phone mode. Note: Please configure the object hwSIPRegisterPhoneNumber after hwSIPRegisterMode has been set to phoneNumber. This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPRegisterPhoneNumber.name: h3cSIPRegisterPhoneNumber
h3cSIPRegisterPhoneNumber.description: The object describes the telephone number which is going to be registered. Note: Please set value of the object h3cIPRegisterMode to phoneNumber before configure this node. This value couldn't be modified unless h3cSIPRegisterEnable is 'off'.

h3cSIPRegisterEnable.name: h3cSIPRegisterEnable
h3cSIPRegisterEnable.description: The object describes register enable or not, default is off. Only if h3cSIPServerConfigTable is configured well, then this node could be set 'on(1)' successfully.

h3cSIPTrapsControl.name: h3cSIPTrapsControl
h3cSIPTrapsControl.description: Indicates whether the SIP module is permitted to generate traps.

h3cSIPStatisticClear.name: h3cSIPStatisticClear
h3cSIPStatisticClear.description: The object is used to clear the statistic information of a SIP gateway. Note: this object only supports set operation.

h3cSIPServerConfigTable.name: h3cSIPServerConfigTable
h3cSIPServerConfigTable.description: A list of the SIP server configuration entries.

h3cSIPServerConfigEntry.name: h3cSIPServerConfigEntry
h3cSIPServerConfigEntry.description: A SIP server configuration entry contains some associated information, e.g. IP address, port, etc.

h3cSIPServerIPAddressType.name: h3cSIPServerIPAddressType
h3cSIPServerIPAddressType.description: The source IP address type of a SIP server.

h3cSIPServerIPAddress.name: h3cSIPServerIPAddress
h3cSIPServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of a SIP server.

h3cSIPServerPort.name: h3cSIPServerPort
h3cSIPServerPort.description: The port of a SIP server.

h3cSIPAcceptType.name: h3cSIPAcceptType
h3cSIPAcceptType.description: The accept type of SIP calls. By default, the object value is all(2).

h3cSIPServerStatus.name: h3cSIPServerStatus
h3cSIPServerStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table. To create a new row, hwSIPServerType must be specified. Note: h3cSIPRegisterEnable must be specifed 'off' before modifing or destroying an existing row or creating a new row.

h3cSIPMsgStatTable.name: h3cSIPMsgStatTable
h3cSIPMsgStatTable.description: A list of SIP message statistics entries.

h3cSIPMsgStatEntry.name: h3cSIPMsgStatEntry
h3cSIPMsgStatEntry.description: A collection of statistics kept for a SIP message.

h3cSIPMsgIndex.name: h3cSIPMsgIndex
h3cSIPMsgIndex.description: The index of a SIP message.

h3cSIPMsgName.name: h3cSIPMsgName
h3cSIPMsgName.description: The name of a SIP message.

h3cSIPMsgSend.name: h3cSIPMsgSend
h3cSIPMsgSend.description: The number of messages which a SIP gateway has sent.

h3cSIPMsgOKSend.name: h3cSIPMsgOKSend
h3cSIPMsgOKSend.description: The number of successful messages which a SIP gateway has sent.

h3cSIPMsgReceive.name: h3cSIPMsgReceive
h3cSIPMsgReceive.description: The number of messages which a SIP gateway has received.

h3cSIPMsgOKReceive.name: h3cSIPMsgOKReceive
h3cSIPMsgOKReceive.description: The number of successful messages which a SIP gateway has received.

h3cSIPMsgResponseStatTable.name: h3cSIPMsgResponseStatTable
h3cSIPMsgResponseStatTable.description: A list of the SIP message response code statistic entries.

h3cSIPMsgResponseStatEntry.name: h3cSIPMsgResponseStatEntry
h3cSIPMsgResponseStatEntry.description: The information of SIP response code.

h3cSIPMsgResponseIndex.name: h3cSIPMsgResponseIndex
h3cSIPMsgResponseIndex.description: The index of a SIP message response code.

h3cSIPResCodeRecvCount.name: h3cSIPResCodeRecvCount
h3cSIPResCodeRecvCount.description: The number of SIP response code which a SIP gateway has received.

h3cSIPResCodeSendCount.name: h3cSIPResCodeSendCount
h3cSIPResCodeSendCount.description: The number of SIP response code which a SIP gateway has sent.

h3cSIPRegisterFailReason.name: h3cSIPRegisterFailReason
h3cSIPRegisterFailReason.description: The object describes the reason that a SIP gateway fails to register.

h3cSIPAuthenReqMethod.name: h3cSIPAuthenReqMethod
h3cSIPAuthenReqMethod.description: The object denotes the method of a request that fails to authenticate.

h3cSIPRegisterFailure.name: h3cSIPRegisterFailure
h3cSIPRegisterFailure.description: The trap is generated when a SIP gateway fails to register.

h3cSIPAuthenticateFailure.name: h3cSIPAuthenticateFailure
h3cSIPAuthenticateFailure.description: The trap is generated when a request with its credential fail to authenticate.

h3cSIPServerSwitch.name: h3cSIPServerSwitch
h3cSIPServerSwitch.description: The trap is generated when a switch happens between master and slave SIP server.
